      { v: "82%", l: "Manual steps removed" },
      { v: "4.2s", l: "Avg document turnaround" },
      { v: "120", l: "Ops headcount supported" },
      { v: "99.4%", l: "Extraction accuracy" }
    ],
    body: [
      "Led the architecture end-to-end: agent graph design, tool contracts, retrieval layer, audit trails. Replaced a spreadsheet-driven review queue with a deterministic state machine that agents operate inside of.",
      "The hardest part wasn't the LLM calls — it was making the system legible to non-technical reviewers. Every agent action is traceable, reversible, and tied back to the source document."
    ]
  },
  {
    num: "02",
    title: "Drupal migration & performance overhaul for a national publisher",
    kicker: "Publishing",
    year: "2024",
    desc: "Migrated a decade of editorial content from a legacy CMS into a custom Drupal architecture. Tuned caching, media pipelines, and search for sub-second response at 500K+ monthly readers.",
    stack: ["Drupal 10", "PHP", "Redis", "Varnish", "Elasticsearch", "Terraform"],
    stats: [
      { v: "500K+", l: "Monthly active readers" },
      { v: "<400ms", l: "P95 page render" },
      { v: "12yr", l: "Archive migrated" },
      { v: "0", l: "Editorial downtime" }
    ],
    body: [
      "Wrote custom migration plugins to normalize 14 content types across three source databases. Editorial could keep publishing in the legacy system until cutover; diffs were reconciled continuously.",
      "Post-launch: custom render cache strategy, image derivatives moved to a CDN pipeline, and search reindexed to Elasticsearch with editor-tunable boosts."
    ]
  },
  {
    num: "03",
    title: "Workflow automation for a government digital service",
    kicker: "Public sector",
    year: "2024",
    desc: "Designed and shipped a set of n8n-backed workflows that eliminated ~80% of the manual back-office work for a citizen-facing service, with a paper trail that holds up to audit.",
    stack: ["n8n", "Node.js", "Symfony", "Postgres", "Docker"],
    stats: [
      { v: "80%+", l: "Manual work removed" },
      { v: "14", l: "Integrated systems" },
      { v: "2.1M", l: "Records processed / yr" },
      { v: "SOC-2", l: "Audit-ready trail" }
    ],
    body: [
      "The brief looked simple — \"automate the forms handling\" — and turned into a full integration project: legacy SOAP endpoints, a GDS design-system front end, and a review board that needed human checkpoints at specific stages.",
      "Shipped as a small set of composable workflows rather than one monolithic pipeline. Each has its own SLA, failure routing, and ownership."
    ]
  },
  {
    num: "04",
    title: "Semantic search & RAG for an e-commerce knowledge base",
    kicker: "E-commerce",
    year: "2023",
    desc: "Replaced a keyword search that was failing support agents with a hybrid semantic + lexical retriever, grounded in a product catalogue of ~40K SKUs and years of ticket history.",
    stack: ["OpenAI", "pgvector", "Python", "FastAPI", "Next.js"],
    stats: [
      { v: "3.8×", l: "Agent-reported accuracy" },
      { v: "40K", l: "SKUs indexed" },
      { v: "220ms", l: "Median query latency" },
      { v: "6wks", l: "Design → prod" }
    ],
    body: [
      "Started with evals: built a labelled set from real tickets before writing a line of retrieval code. That dataset is what told us when the hybrid scoring was actually winning and when it was just drifting.",
      "Deployed behind a thin internal UI that agents already knew. No training needed — the old search box just got better."
    ]
